"v.驱逐，击退；厌恶；n.驱逐，击退，厌恶 【英】 v. 驱逐，击退(repel)；厌恶(to repel by discourtesy, coldness, or denial)；n. 驱逐，击退，厌恶 (rebuff, rejection) 【考】 反义词：captivate( 使着迷); court(追求); entrance(使入神) 【记】 re(反)+pulse(推)→ 推出去→击退 【例】 The army repulsed the rebels. v. /n. 驱逐, 击退; 使...产生反感 【记】re反, pulse推－反推出去－击退; 反感 【反】captivate(v 迷住); entrance(v 使入神); court(v 追求)－repulse intentionally(有意反感) 【记】源自repel(击退，使厌恶) pul=pel；re反 + pulse (脉搏，脉冲)看成 push 力，反推 【相关】compulsion=compel,expulse=expel；impulse=impel；propulsive=propel；repulse=repel repulse (v.)  early 15c., from Latin repulsus, past participle of repellere ""drive back, reject"" (see repel). Related: Repulsed; repulsing.  repulse (n.)  1530s, from Latin repulsa ""refusal, denial,"" noun use of fem. past participle of repellere (see repel)."
